⁣⁣⁣
Keto Creme Brulee⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Making use of my leftover egg yolks, I made these. No blowtorch so last 5 mins I turned the temperature to 210 degree, sprinkled a bit of lakanto on each ramekin and shifted the baking tray to the top (I sprinkled 1 tbsp of lakanto for all instead of 1 tbsp each). ⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣
Ingredients:⁣⁣
4 egg yolks⁣⁣
1 tsp vanilla extract⁣⁣
2 cups HWC⁣⁣
2 tbsp lakanto⁣⁣
⁣🔺I used a big and a small ramekin. ⁣⁣
⁣
⁣
Instructions:⁣⁣
1. Preheat oven to 170 degree. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
2. Whisk egg yolks and vanilla extract in a bowl.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
3. Pour HWC and 1 tbsp lakanto into a saucepan over medium heat. Whisk constantly until it starts to simmer. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
4. Remove from heat, add yolk mixture and whisk constantly, until well combined. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
5. Divide evenly between 4 ramekins and place them in a baking dish, pour in enough boiling water to 1 inch up to the sides of the ramekins.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
6. Bake in the preheated oven on the middle rack until set, about 30 minutes.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
7. Last 5 mins, sprinkle 1 tbsp lakanto over those Creme Brulee (This method to skip blowtorch) ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
8. Turn the temperature to 210 degree and shift the baking tray carefully to the top. ⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
⁣⁣⁣
Recipe adapted from: https://www.allrecipes.com/recipe/261027/keto-creme-brulee/⁣⁣⁣
